posts.raw_content:
I suffer from rosacea that was just diagnosed as cystic acne as a child.  Dermatologist kept recommending antibiotics which did nothing and just upset my stomach until eventually we switched to Acutane.  Acutane completely destroyed my skin biome, but it also meant that acne couldn't grow.

Anyways I moved away from home for about 15 years and never had a problem again.  Recently I moved to a house back near I grew up.  My skin rosacea slowly crept back, but I had dealt with worse as a teenager so I ignored it.

Three years ago the cystic acne came back here and there, but never bad enough to go back on a drug for it.  I've tried dozens of products from Ulta.

It's finally reached a breaking point to where I was about to set up an appointment with my GP to get a recommendation for a Dermatologist and go back on the antibiotics.  

I caught a conversation on here talking about using the horse paste cream on your skin which I had never thought of.  I found my local CVS had a Ivermectic cream for lice and so I spent 40 bucks figuring why the hell not.

This is the first night that I have not felt a zit growing on my face in atleast a year, probably closer to two

I started looking more into it, and it was most likely brought on by my sensitivity to Oak Pollen which I moved back to 6 years ago

It was exasperated by some crazy vacations 4 years ago when I did a bit of a walk about and got sunburned

And it may be cured from just 10 minutes of it on my face using it as directed

best internet community out there <3
